HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 141
By Warner
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Catherine Hazlerig on
her selection as the 2024–2025 Longview
Elementary School Teacher of the Year.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
specially recognize those outstanding education professionals who have devoted their careers
to providing the highest-quality education for Tennessee's students; and
WHEREAS, Catherine Hazlerig is one such estimable individual, who has distinguished
herself as a professional of the greatest dedication, ability, and integrity; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Hazlerig has been selected as the 2024–2025 Longview Elementary
School Teacher of the Year, a most befitting honor that recognizes the positive influence she
has on so many young lives; and
WHEREAS, Catherine Hazlerig is an extremely talented and compassionate person who
works assiduously to motivate her students to reach their full potential, both as scholars and as
citizens; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Hazlerig serves as an inspiration to her colleagues and students alike,
and her friendship and counsel are highly valued by those who are fortunate to know her; and
WHEREAS, Catherine Hazlerig truly epitomizes the dedicated education professional
who is wholly committed to the highest ideals of public service and quality education for all, and
she should be specially recognized; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we hereby honor and congratulate Catherine Hazlerig on being chosen as
the 2024–2025 Longview Elementary School Teacher of the Year, commend her exceptional
